				<textElement textAlignment="Justified" markup="html">
					<font size="10"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[<b>1.3</b> The Loan will be utilized for the purpose for which it is sanctioned as per the Loan Approval Letter and granted as per the Loan Agreement based on the information provided by the Borrower/s in the Application Form / Project Report. Purpose of the Loan shall not be changed in any manner during the Loan and any such change in Purpose shall take place onlywith the prior written permission of the Company. The Borrower will provide to the Company all the necessary documents as may be required by the Company. The Company shall have the right to appoint auditors to certify the end use of the Loan.<br>
<b>1.4</b> The Loan will be repaid by the Borrower/s by way of EMIs and at the rate of interest arrived in accordance with the terms and conditions in this Agreement and the Schedule annexed hereto. The Borrower shall also pay such processing fees, other costs, charges and expenses as detailed hereinafter. Each EMI shall be calculated based on the monthly rests. The company has right to revise interest rate depending on prevailing market rate, if borrower agreed upon for Floating Rate of Interest.<br>
<b>1.5</b> Time is of the essence of the contract.<br>
<b>1.6</b> Borrower hereby agrees that the credit facility hereby granted is solely at the discretion of the Company and may include approvals or disallowance of facilities, such as:<br><br>
a) Drawings beyond the sanctioned limits.<br>
b) Drawings when the Borrower’s account is classified as a Non Performing Asset (NPA) or due to non-compliance of the terms of sanction. Borrower further agrees that the Company does not have any obligation to meet further requirement on account of growth in business without fresh review of credit limits.<br>
<b>1.7</b> The Borrower shall not be entitled to cancel the facility granted under this Agreement or refuse to accept the disbursements under the present Agreement. Any cancellation of the facility under the present Agreement shall be subject to the payment of the Prepayment Charges as mentioned in the Schedule and as may be required by the Company from time to time.<br>]]></text>
			</staticText>
