				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[2.1 FLOATING RATE OF INTEREST (FROI):]]></text>
			</staticText>
			<staticText>
				<reportElement x="60" y="520" width="467" height="180" uuid="54e02ad3-f0b8-4b35-b3bc-45d0150ff4aa"/>
				<textElement markup="html"/>
				<text><![CDATA[<b>1.</b> If the rate of interest applicable to the Borrower/s is Floating Rate of Interest, thefollowing shall apply;<br>
<b>a.</b> The FROI shall be changed within each Reset Period, based on the then prevailing Index rate or Prime lending rate and the Borrower/s shall thereafter pay interest on the loan at such new rate. The Company will change the rate on the first day of the month/ bi monthly / quarterly /half yearly following the Reset period in which the Index / Base rate or Prime lending rate is changed.<br>
<b>b.</b> If the Company changes the FROI prior to the disbursement of the full facility within Reset period, the weighted average of the different FROI shall be applicable to the Facility forthwith from the date of such increase or decrease till the first day of the month following the Reset period in which Index / Base rate or Prime Lending rate is changed.<br>
<b>c.</b> The FROI to the facility shall be on the basis of Index / Base rate or Prime lending rate prevailing on the date of final disbursement<br>
